{"text": "You certainly won't be taking any risks playing   especially considering it‚Äôs free.   This visual novel is a cute, light hearted and short experience and despite the high school setting being one that‚Äôs used a lot, the overall plot is a little more unique.   It features beautiful art, adventures and of course, adorable love stories! It‚Äôs realistic in the way that college students get pretty stressed during their exams and want to find a fun outlet. That outlet is usually partying but, in this case, it‚Äôs trespassing on old, abandoned buildings! I can‚Äôt say I‚Äôd recommend doing that but whatever floats your boat.  The MC, Alex is seen as being very human; she‚Äôs lonely and craves more (well, any type of) social interaction and when she finds it, she‚Äôs happier. She‚Äôs aware of her feelings but doesn‚Äôt always know how to act on them. She‚Äôs nervous, excitable and fearful. I found her enjoyable to play as. She was a nice contrast to a lot of the bland mc‚Äôs out there.   The LI‚Äôs also have their own realistic struggles that make them feel more alive and relatable without taking it to the extreme.   I don‚Äôt think I need to say more! ;p", "appid": "1274200", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044949801", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589198400.0}
